[
    {
        "id": "59da63b5adb460db",
        "type": "tab",
        "label": "[split] Array type",
        "disabled": false,
        "info": "## Split lists\n\nLists are the Erlang array types and these can either be strings or lists of things - so what the split node does is differentiate between array lenghts:\n\n- fixed length of 0 - array is treated as a string and is split using the char marker, e.g., `\\n`.\n\n- fixed length of 1 - array is assumed to be an array of arrays and is split by element,\n\n- fixed length > 1 - array is assumed to be a string and is split by the fixed value.\n\nNegative lengths aren't allowed, else they would also have a meaning.",
        "env": [
